    <p>BLOCK: Congressman Cantor, I want to ask you about a separate financial package heading your way, and that's the stimulus package. The Democrats' proposal looks to be about $825 billion; it breaks down as about two-thirds of spending, one-third in tax cuts. Do you see that as being about the right balance?</p>
    <p>NORRIS: I think that that question is the wrong jumping-off point.</p>
    <p>BLOCK: Uh-huh.</p>
