    <p>MYERS: Well, Melissa, I think it's as close as any state may have gotten in modern times. You know, California's $40 billion deficit is larger than any deficit any state faces in the nation, at least in dollar terms. And really, it's a real double whammy. It's the result of the real major economic crisis we're all suffering through, and from California's long-running political fight about how to balance a budget for a state with 38 million people.</p>
