    <p>MYERS: The Democrats here in California want more of the solution to be taxes, the Republicans want no new taxes. And I think the real question is which is worse - deep cuts in state spending which would affect the social safety net in these economically troubling times, or a tax increase during bad times that could further slow the economy. The governor seems to be stuck in the middle of a battle where everyone sees what to do differently.</p>
