    <p>Mr. STEVE YOUNG (NFL Player): If I can take 20 seconds to help them make their rent, if I knew that story, then I'd do it everyday, right? I mean that's easy. </p>
    <p>PESCA: It must be an odd thing to know that with a flick of a pen you can make someone a $100, unless, once upon a time with the toss of a ball, you made someone millions. Mike Pesca, NPR News, Tampa, Florida. </p>
<h1> "Parting Words" </h1>
    <p>JACKI LYDEN, Host: And we have parting words today from the 19th-century satirist Ambrose Bierce, who wrote, Mark how my fame rings out from zone to zone, a thousand critics shouting, He's unknown. But we hope we're not unknown in your end zone. That's All Things Considered from NPR News. I'm Jacki Lyden. </p>
